{"lemma": "مَخاضٌ", "slug": "مَخاضٌ", "root": "م.خ.ض", "root_slug": "م-خ-ض", "root_link": "/words/roots/م-خ-ض", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "مَخاض", "root": "مخض", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n38284", "n11707", "n38285"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "labour pains", "fa": "درد زایمان", "ur": "زچگی کا درد", "tr": "doğum sancısı", "id": "nyeri persalinan", "bn": "প্রসবের ব্যথা", "es": "dolores del parto", "fr": "douleurs de l'accouchement", "de": "Wehen", "ru": "родовые схватки", "zh": "分娩痛"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "labour pains", "examples": [{"text": "فَأَجَاۤءَهَا ٱلۡمَخَاضُ إِلَىٰ جِذۡعِ ٱلنَّخۡلَةِ قَالَتۡ یَـٰلَیۡتَنِی مِتُّ قَبۡلَ هَـٰذَا وَكُنتُ نَسۡیࣰا مَّنسِیࣰّا", "english": "Then the pains of labour drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She cried, “Alas! I wish I had died before this, and was a thing long forgotten!”"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of مَخَاضَة (maḵāḍa)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ma.xaːdˤ/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n38284", "headword_ar": "مَخَاضٌ", "root": "mxD", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pains of parturition;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mixaADN", "text_ar": "مِخَاضٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.)       -A2-  Applied to she-camels, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Pregnant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, As, S, ISd, A, Msb, K, &c.:) used in this sense as an epithet of good omen, whence they augur that their young ones will become agitated in their bellies at the time of parturition: (ISd:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having their young in their bellies:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as are called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei$aAr", "text_ar": "عِشَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that have been ten months pregnant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th, K:) but ISd says, I have not found this explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mxAD", "text_ar": "مخاض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "on any authority beside that of Th: (TA:) [see also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eu$araA='u", "text_ar": "عُشَرَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] it has no proper sing: (S:) a single one is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xalifapN", "text_ar": "خَلِفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (AZ, As, S, A, &c,) which is extr. (K, TA) with respect to rule: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaADN", "text_ar": "مَخَاضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies, or it signifies also, (accord. to different copies of the K,) she-camels"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the state in which they are from the time when the stallion is sent among them"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISd, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until he brays"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hat~aY yahodira", "text_ar": "حَتَّى يَهْدِرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), or, accord. to another relation,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until they are left"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ht~Y tugodara", "text_ar": "حتّى تُغْدَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), i.e., (ISd,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until he ceases"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ht~Y", "text_ar": "حتّى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yanoqaTiEa", "text_ar": "يَنْقَطِعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the copies of the K, erroneously,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HtY tnqTE", "text_ar": "حتى تنقطع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from covering:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISd, K:) a pl. (K) having no sing. (ISd, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (S,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aibonu maxaADK", "text_ar": "اِبْنُ مَخَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A young male camel, which,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having completed a year"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, Mgh)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the day of its birth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has entered upon the second year:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, Mgh, Msb, K:) because his mother, (S, IAth, Mgh, K,) from whom he has been separated, (S,) has become adjoined to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaAD", "text_ar": "مَخَاض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, IAth, Mgh, K,) or pregnant camels, (IAth, K,) whether she have conceived or not; (S, IAth, * K; *) for they used to make the stallion-camels to cover the females a year after these had brought forth, (IAth, K, *) in order that their young ones might become strong, so that they conceived in the second year: (IAth:) or because its mother has been covered, and has conceived, and become adjoined to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaAD", "text_ar": "مَخَاض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i.e., to the pregnant camels; and this appellation it bears"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until it has completed the second year;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but when it has entered upon the third, it is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aibonu labuwnK", "text_ar": "اِبْنُ لَبُونٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a young male camel when his mother has conceived:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whose mother has become pregnant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when the she-camels among whom is his mother have become pregnant, though she have not become so:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, K:) the female is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "binotu maxaADK", "text_ar": "بِنْتُ مَخَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (IAth, Msb, K;) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aibonapu", "text_ar": "اِبْنَةُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaADK", "text_ar": "مَخَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) the pl., (S, Msb, K,) of both the male and female appellations, (Msb,) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAtu", "text_ar": "بَنَاتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaADK", "text_ar": "مَخَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) only; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAtu labuwnK", "text_ar": "بَنَاتُ لَبُونٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "banaAtu A=waY", "text_ar": "بَنَاتُ ا=وَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) Sometimes one adds to it the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aibonu AlmaxaADi", "text_ar": "اِبْنُ المَخَاضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) [for]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Abn mxAD", "text_ar": "ابن مخاض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is indeterminate; and when you desire to make it determinate, you affix the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as above; but this only makes it determinate as a generic appellation. (S.)"}], "source_refs": ["ISd", "M", "TA", "Th", "K", "S", "As", "Mgh", "Msb", "IAth"]}, {"entry_id": "n11707", "headword_ar": "مَخَاضٌ", "root": "xwD", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaADapN", "text_ar": "مَخَاضَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n38285", "headword_ar": "مِخَاضٌ", "root": "mxD", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maxaADN", "text_ar": "مَخَاضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}